Ahora construiremos una función para obtener las métricas.

In [ ]:
def metricas_train_val(y_train, y_train_predict,y_val, y_val_predict):
    '''
    y_train: variable a predecir en entrenamiento
    y_train_predict : variable predicha en entrenamiento
    y_val : variable a predecir en validación
    y_val_predict: variable predicha en validación
    
    Hace uso de la función 'metricas' para los valores reales y predichos
    de validación y entrenamiento

    '''
    def metricas(y, y_pred,train_val):

        '''
        y: variable a predecir
        y_pred : variable predicha
        train_val: caracter para decidir si es entrenamiento o validación
        
        
        Hace uso de la función 'metricas' para los valores reales y predichos
        de validación y entrenamiento

        '''
        # MAE train
        mae = mean_absolute_error(y, y_pred)
        # R2 train
        r2 = r2_score(y, y_pred)
        # MAPE train
        mape= mean_absolute_percentage_error(y, y_pred)
        # MSE train
        mse = mean_squared_error(y, y_pred)
        # RMSE train
        rmse = mean_squared_error(y, y_pred, squared=False)

        metrics = {
            "": [train_val],
            "rmse": [rmse],
            "mse": [mse],
            "r2": [r2],
            "mae": [mae],
            "mape": [mape]
        }
        metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics)
        
        return metrics_df

    metricas_train = metricas(y_train, y_train_predict,'Train')
    metricas_test = metricas(y_val, y_val_predict,'Val')
    metric = pd.concat([metricas_train, metricas_test], ignore_index=True)
    
    return metric

In [ ]:
# Transforma X_train y val en dataframes, entrena varios modelos con diferentes variables y mide varias métricas
X_train_df = pd.DataFrame(X_train, columns=X.columns)
X_test_df = pd.DataFrame(X_val, columns=X.columns)
dataset_seleccion = pd.DataFrame()

for i in range(1, len(X_train_df.columns)):
    sbs = SFS(LinearRegression(), k_features=i, forward=False, floating=False)
    sbs.fit(np.array(X_train), y_train)
    sbs.k_feature_names_
    regression = LinearRegression()
    selected_features = [X_train_df.columns[int(index)] for index in list(sbs.k_feature_idx_)]
    regression.fit(X_train_df[selected_features], y_train)
    y_pred = regression.predict(X_test_df[selected_features])

    # Calcular métricas
    mse = mean_squared_error(y_test, y_pred)
    rmse = np.sqrt(mse)
    r2 = r2_score(y_test, y_pred)
    mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)
    y_test = np.array(y_test)
    mape = np.mean(np.abs((y_test - y_pred) / y_test)) * 100

    # Crear un DataFrame con las métricas
    metrics = {
        "variables": [selected_features],
        "rmse": [rmse],
        "mse": [mse],
        "r2": [r2],
        "mae": [mae],
        "mape": [mape]
    }
    metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics)

    # Concatenar al dataset_seleccion
    dataset_seleccion = pd.concat([dataset_seleccion, metrics_df], ignore_index=True)

Creamos una función para obtener las métricas en test

In [ ]:
def metricas(y, y_pred):
    '''
    y: variable a predecir
    y_pred : variable predicha
        
    Hace uso de la función 'metricas' para los valores reales y predichos
    de validación y entrenamiento
    '''

    # MAE train
    mae = mean_absolute_error(y, y_pred)
    # R2 train
    r2 = r2_score(y, y_pred)
    # MAPE train
    mape= mean_absolute_percentage_error(y, y_pred)
    # MSE train
    mse = mean_squared_error(y, y_pred)
    # RMSE train
    rmse = mean_squared_error(y, y_pred, squared=False)

    metrics = {
        "": ['test'],
        "rmse": [rmse],
        "mse": [mse],
        "r2": [r2],
        "mae": [mae],
        "mape": [mape]
    }
    metrics_df = pd.DataFrame(metrics)
        
    return metrics_df
In [ ]:
